PROJECT MASTER DIRECTIVE: GREEN MACHINE ($10M AUM)
1. USER IDENTITY & CONTEXT

User: Marcelo, Senior Quantitative Software Engineer.

Objective: Developing "Green Machine," a high-fidelity backtesting and execution engine for a $10,000,000 AUM fund.

Specialization: SPY 0DTE/Short-term Put and Call scalping.

Data Depth: Historical analysis from 1993 to Present (Regime-based logic).

2. HARDWARE & ARCHITECTURE CONSTRAINTS

Backend (PC): Dual GPU (32GB VRAM), TimescaleDB for time-series Greeks, Rust-based backtester for speed.

Frontend (MacBook): React/Vite minimalist dashboard, "Glass Cockpit" aesthetic, WebSocket-driven.

Alerts: Telegram/Discord Bot integration for mobile trade signals during work hours.

3. SYSTEM-WIDE STANDARDS (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

Risk Management: Always assume institutional slippage and market impact for $10M orders. Implement Daily/Monthly drawdown circuit breakers.

Performance: Python code must be vectorized (NumPy/Pandas). Rust core must prioritize SIMD operations.

Logic: Use "Regime Detection" (e.g., comparing current market to 2008 or 2020) for every strategy proposal.

Style: High-contrast, minimalist, Bloomberg-style UI. No "retail" fluff.

4. INTERACTION RULES

No Junior Code: Avoid basic tutorials. Provide production-ready, thread-safe, and scalable solutions.

Conciseness: Be brief. Focus on logic and execution over prose.

Integrity: If a proposed trade strategy has a Max Drawdown > 12% or a Sharp Ratio < 2.0, flag it as "High Risk/Unsuitable."

5. REPOSITORY LAYOUT (monorepo)

engine/       — PC: FastAPI + Python backtester; Rust execution core under engine/rust_executioner/
pilot/        — MacBook: React/Vite Glass Cockpit
historian/    — PC: Timescale SQL (historian/sql), ingest & seed scripts (historian/scripts), future training
docs/         — API_CONTRACT.md, STRATEGY_DIRECTIVE.md
data/         — Local SQLite (greenmachine.db) and future transaction DBs (*.db gitignored)
